																					<div class="question-area">
												<span class="question bold">What does the market price represent?</span>
												<div class="answer-wrapper">
																																										<p>The market price displays how many units of the secondary currency of the pair is equivalent to 1 unit of the first currency of the pair. For example, if EURUSD is trading at 1.12000, that means for every 1 Euro (first currency of the pair) you would receive / require 1.12 USD.</p>
																																							</div>
											</div>
																					<div class="question-area">
												<span class="question bold">What type of spreads are offered by <?php echo(strip_tags($platform_name))?>?</span>
												<div class="answer-wrapper">
																																										<p>All of our account types have variable (floating) spreads. This means that the spread will differ based on the prices we are receiving from our deep pool of Liquidity Providers and will reflect the market conditions of the underlying asset at that specific time.</p>
																																							</div>
											</div>
																					<div class="question-area">
												<span class="question bold">What are the fees for trading with <?php echo(strip_tags($platform_name))?>?</span>
